<p><b>Michael Gordon Oldfield</b> (born 15 May 1953) is an <a href="England" title="England">English</a> <a href="Multi-instrumentalist" title="Multi-instrumentalist">multi-instrumentalist</a> musician and composer, working a style that blends <a href="Progressive_rock" title="Progressive rock">progressive rock</a>, <a href="Folk_music" title="Folk music">folk</a>, ethnic or <a href="World_music" title="World music">world music</a>, <a href="Classical_music" title="Classical music">classical music</a>, <a href="Electronic_music" title="Electronic music">electronic music</a>, <a href="New_Age_music" title="New Age music">New Age</a>, and more recently, <a href="Dance_music" title="Dance music">dance</a>. His music is often elaborate and complex in nature. He is best known for his 1973 hit album <i><a href="Tubular_Bells" title="Tubular Bells">Tubular Bells</a></i>, which launched <a href="Virgin_Records" title="Virgin Records">Virgin Records</a>, and for his 1983 hit single "<a href="Moonlight_Shadow" title="Moonlight Shadow">Moonlight Shadow</a>".<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He is also well known for his hit rendition of the Christmas piece "<a href="In_Dulci_Jubilo_/_On_Horseback" title="In Dulci Jubilo / On Horseback">In Dulci Jubilo</a>".</p>
